9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 786, L.D. 1181, “An Act Regarding the
10 Designation of Short-term Rental Units as Commercial or Residential in Use”
11 Amend the bill in section 1 in subsection 2 in the 3rd line (page 1, line 6 in L.D.) by
12 striking out the following: "requiring" and inserting the following: 'allowing'
13 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
14 number to read consecutively.
15 SUMMARY
1166 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, clarifies that a
1177 municipality may establish a regulation that allows, but does not require, the municipal
1188 assessor to assign land use codes that designate short-term rental units as commercial in
1199 use or residential in use.
